# Error Handling Rules

## Backend: ApiError

All business errors use the shared `ApiError` utility. Never throw generic `Error`.

```ts
// src/utils/ApiError.ts
import { HttpException } from '@nestjs/common';

export class ApiError extends HttpException {
  constructor(status: number, message: string) {
    super({ success: false, statusCode: status, message }, status);
  }
}
```

---

## Standard Error Codes

```ts
throw new ApiError(400, 'Invalid request data');         // Bad Request
throw new ApiError(401, 'Unauthorized');                 // Missing/invalid token
throw new ApiError(403, 'Permission denied');            // Valid token, wrong role
throw new ApiError(404, 'User not found');              // Resource missing
throw new ApiError(409, 'Email already exists');         // Conflict
throw new ApiError(422, 'Cannot cancel a paid order');  // Business rule violation
throw new ApiError(429, 'Too many requests');            // Rate limited
throw new ApiError(500, 'Something went wrong');        // Unexpected error
```

---

## Global Exception Filter

Catches ALL unhandled exceptions and formats them consistently:

```ts
@Catch()
export class GlobalExceptionFilter implements ExceptionFilter {
  catch(exception: unknown, host: ArgumentsHost): void {
    // Maps HttpException, Prisma errors, and unknown errors
    // Returns: { success: false, statusCode, message, timestamp, path }
  }
}
```

Register in `main.ts`:
```ts
app.useGlobalFilters(new GlobalExceptionFilter());
```

---

## Service Error Pattern

```ts
// ✅ Service throws ApiError — controller does not catch it
async findOne(id: string) {
  const user = await this.userDb.findById(id);
  if (!user) throw new ApiError(404, 'User not found');
  return user;
}

// ❌ Never
async findOne(id: string) {
  try {
    const user = await this.userDb.findById(id);
    return user ?? null;
  } catch {
    return null; // silent failure
  }
}
```

---

## Prisma Error Mapping

Handle in `GlobalExceptionFilter`:

| Prisma Code | Meaning                          | HTTP Status |
|-------------|----------------------------------|-------------|
| P2002       | Unique constraint violation      | 409         |
| P2025       | Record not found                 | 404         |
| P2003       | Foreign key constraint failure   | 400         |
| P2014       | Relation violation               | 400         |

